			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Taunting, bards just don't get it<a name="26401"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 9 04 11:44 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>(ok, pun intended with subject...)
<br />

<br />
I know, it's been asked for many times, but is there a reason that bards havent gotten a taunt song/skill yet? We needed the detaunt song at one point, but now it seems that there are many times I'd rather get the mobs attention, such as giving the cleric that extract 1.5 seconds to camp (3 ticks if deftdance is up), or just to split mobs for CC (65 mez doesnt pull, which is good and bad). 
<br />

<br />
LOL, ok, as I post this, I actually think I know why it would be WAY too abusable if we got a taunt song...Selo's. Unless the song had a VERY small range, about equal to bellow or less, and a semi-long recast timer, we could keep aggro and have the group use ranged attacks with minimal risk...
<br />

<br />
GRR, ok, how about just giving bards the blinking TAUNT skill?? Novel idea (not), but it certainly fits into the class description, and shouldn't really be abusable. Better yet, with the new melee skill feature, give us a taunt skill that drains endurance. Have it cost enough that if we are using it frequently, we won't have enough endurance for deftdance/puretone.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, this topic has been posted to death, sorry. Any chance SOE ever officially commented if bards were explicitly excluded from deliberately gaining taunt for some balance reason? 
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="//www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=667584">Mithrus Wulfsong</a><br>
