				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Taunting, bards just don't get it<a name="26406"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 9 04 11:51 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Need aggro?  Gotta let the cleric camp?
<br />

<br />
DA song, click it off, and run with the MOBS.  Since they can't hit the rest of the group, they follow you.  If you can run for the full duration of the song, that means it's 18 seconds before the cleric is vulnerable again, and the MOBs have just run directly away from the cleric for the past 18 seconds....so 36 total seconds for the cleric to camp in.  
<br />

<br />
Of course, if you get bardbecued when you click DA off, it won't help the group much...risk we all take.
<br />

<br />
If you want to make sure that you get aggro for deftdance, though, here's a trick: sit down.  You still dodge frontal attacks at least.</span></td>
