				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Taunting, bards just don't get it<a name="26633"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 10 04 8:51 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Aye, after thinking on it some more, we need a taunt skill, not a song. I think even the standard taunt skill that other melees get would work just fine. 
<br />

<br />
I like the idea of using our endurance bar more, and therefore could have it generate more hate, with the tradeoff being it can't be used ALL the time. I also like the idea limiting it to non-animal and non-undead, which would help create more balance, and keeping it realistic (bards are skilled at affecting moods, which don't exactly apply to animals and undead).
<br />

<br />
Hmm, here's a cool derivation: have two taunt skills, one that drains endurance, and the other draining mana (more mystical in nature). The second version could work on anything perhaps, or increases the hate more, or maybe targeted/PB aoe.
<br />
</span></td>
