Ive been in a recent group with a Warrior, SK, Bard (me), Bard (someone else), Cleric, and Shaman.
<br />

<br />
When I pull LDoN, I pull at 50%. I pull with selo's constant chain. The reason I do this is to give the tank a snared mob to cast his agro spells, target, etc, etc, etc... just makes things a tad easier IMO. I usually have my pulls down to where Im with the group and singing mana again when we get the exp hit and the other mob is about 15 feet away walking slowly... anyhow, thats not all that relivant (spelling?).
<br />

<br />
I do this and get <i>behind</i> the SK tank.... he then watches... pivots his body as the mob passes him... then starts to autoattack when the mob gets to me and proceeds to beat on me. If you think 70-80% is bad... this tank didnt get agro until I left to pull another mob at 50%. I dont think this has so much to do with me being uber as it does with the tank just plain sucking <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-14.gif" border="0" alt="Devil" hspace="2" /></span></td>
